# No Shortcuts / Complete Work

It must be easier to do the right thing than to bypass checks.

## Forbidden escapes

- `@ts-ignore`, `@ts-expect-error`, `@ts-nocheck`
- `eslint-disable`, `eslint-disable-next-line`, `eslint-disable-line`
- `any`, type assertions (`as Type`), non-null assertions (`!`)
- Note: `as const` (const assertions) is allowed — e.g. query key factories
- Skipping or disabling tests (`it.skip`, `describe.only`, etc.)
- Leaving TODO/FIXME that encode unfinished work or tech debt
- `--no-verify` on git hooks

## Config files are locked

Do **not** edit these to work around typing or lint errors:

- `eslint.config.js`
- `tsconfig.json`, `tsconfig.app.json`, `tsconfig.node.json`

Only change them when the user **explicitly** asks (e.g. “change the eslint rules”, “relax tsconfig”). On type/lint failures: fix the application code, not the tooling.

## Complete every task to 100%

Before finishing any change:

1. Types compile (`pnpm tsc`)
2. Lint is clean (`pnpm lint`, `--max-warnings 0`)
3. Tests pass (`pnpm test`) — add/update tests when behavior changes
4. Docs and `.cursor/rules` updated if conventions changed
5. `pnpm validate` is green

If something cannot be finished now: **stop and ask** — do not ship partial work that accumulates debt.
